Wumpus World implementation uses a FastAPI backend and an enterprise-styled frontend to simulate agent navigation through a hazardous grid. The agent starts at $(0,0)$ and explores the environment by clicking cells, with the system tracking visited locations and updating a "Safe Cells Logged" score. If the agent triggers a hidden pit, the system status immediately switches from ACTIVE to TERMINATED, revealing the hazard and locking all further inputs until a manual reset is performed via the dashboard. The project is structured as a single-file application requiring only fastapi and uvicorn to run.
